<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The HTTP/1.1 Spec states that messages header field values may be preceded by any amount of LWS ( <a href="http://www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec4.html#sec4.2">http://w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/â€¦</a> ). The Curl adapter checks if a message is chunked by doing a string position check for "Transfer-Encoding: chunked\r\n", which will not detect valid headers with excess whitespace like "Transfer-Encoding:    chunked\r\n". If this check succeeds, it removes the header as Curl automatically handles chunked messages.</p>

<p>This results in the Zend_Http_Response trying to decode the message as if it were chunked and throwing an error that the message doesn't appear to be chunked.</p>

